article_title: Kansas man killed in Nebraska crash
article_text:
Authorities say a Kansas man has been killed in a south-central Nebraska highway crash.

The accident was reported around 5 p.m. Wednesday on Nebraska Highway 78, east of Red Cloud in Webster County.

The Lincoln Journal Star reports that the Webster County Sheriff's Office identified the victim as 75-year-old George Pfrimmer, of Mankato, Kansas.
